      "@context": "http://www.w3.org/ns/anno.jsonld",
      "type": "Annotation",
      "body": [
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "purpose": "transcribing",
          "value": "Every word of one's prayer should be like a rose that is picked from a bush. One gathers rose upon\nrose until a bouquet is formed and can be offered to God as a beautiful blessing.\nNachman of Bratzlav\nGod has placed abilities and challenges in our heart, without regard to gender. Each of us has the\nduty, whether man or woman, to realize those gifts God has given. Regina Jonas",
          "language": "en"
        }
      ],
